        <p>Hello, I’m Wilbur Suero</p>
        
        <p>
          I’m a <strong>Staff Backend Engineer</strong> specializing in <strong>Distributed Systems, Applied AI, and Ruby on Rails</strong>. I design and scale B2B products, build data-heavy architectures, and engineer production LLM-driven workflows that power conversational AI and analytics at scale.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently, I work at <strong>Puzzle</strong>, where I own and ship production AI features supporting tens of thousands of daily users. 
        </p>
        <p>
          I am also the founder and principal engineer of <a href="https://proxypattern.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">ProxyPattern</a>, a boutique engineering studio that partners with founders and CTOs to design scalable backend architectures, optimize databases, and implement production-grade AI systems.
        </p>
        
        <blockquote>
          “No Magic, Just Systems.”
        </blockquote>

        <p>
          <strong>My engineering worldview is simple: I am the engineer who removes complexity from complex systems.</strong> Most software engineering problems aren't solved by writing clever, hyper-complicated code—they are solved by choosing the right abstractions, understanding database index behaviors, and building clean, predictable systems that human operators can maintain without getting paged in the middle of the night.
        </p>

        <h2 id="what-i-do">What I do</h2>
        <p>
          I focus on building software that solves expensive problems. I ensure backend systems stay <strong>correct under concurrency</strong>, stay <strong>fast under high load</strong>, and remain <strong>predictable and debuggable</strong> at scale—translating directly into reduced infrastructure bills and higher operational uptime.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most of my daily work centers around the intersection of <strong>applied AI and backend infrastructure</strong>. I obsess over production constraints: optimizing background processing (Sidekiq, Redis, Elixir services), reducing LLM API inference latency by 60%, and slashing token costs through caching, batching, and early-exit execution flows to maintain high reliability and cost-efficiency.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background includes a deep foundation in graphic design and multimedia, having graduated from the <strong>Altos de Chavón School of Design</strong> and <strong>ITLA</strong>. This unique design-leaning perspective gives me a high standard for usability, responsive interfaces, and developer experience—bridging the gap between robust system engineering and visual product execution.
        </p>

